1
00:00:01,793 --> 00:00:03,253
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:18,047 --> 00:01:20,150
[theme music concludes]

3
00:01:22,541 --> 00:01:28,505
ASSAULT

4
00:01:40,601 --> 00:01:42,561
Regarding Naomi Misora's disappearance,

5
00:01:43,145 --> 00:01:45,314
shouldn't we open
an investigation into this matter?

6
00:01:45,378 --> 00:01:48,339
[Ryuzaki] If we do, it should be
coordinated separately from the Kira case.

7
00:01:48,439 --> 00:01:51,445
Also, we'll have to use police sketches
instead of actual photos.

8
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:54,197
We're talking about someone who's been
missing for four months already.

9
00:01:54,281 --> 00:01:55,929
Chances are she's probably dead.

10
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:58,285
If you're right about that,

11
00:01:58,410 --> 00:02:00,871
I find it odd
that we haven't found her body yet.

12
00:02:01,161 --> 00:02:04,374
If we did, it might provide us
with some much-needed physical evidence.

13
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:05,459
[door opens]

14
00:02:05,584 --> 00:02:07,252
-[Watari] Ryuzaki.
-Hm?

15
00:02:07,336 --> 00:02:09,880
Something seems to be happening
on Sakura TV.

16
00:02:10,756 --> 00:02:11,840
In other words,

17
00:02:11,923 --> 00:02:14,343
all of the reporters and staff here
are Kira's hostages.

18
00:02:14,468 --> 00:02:16,511
Aside from that,
we have a professional obligation…

19
00:02:16,595 --> 00:02:17,971
MESSAGE FROM KIRA
FOUR VIDEOS

20
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:20,307
…to share this message with you.
I assure you that this is not a hoax.

21
00:02:20,432 --> 00:02:24,811
And that Sakura TV is not airing this tape
for the purposes of sensationalism.

22
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:26,229
[Aizawa] "Kira's hostages"?

23
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:27,481
[Matsuda] What is this?

24
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:31,068
[man on TV] Four days ago,
our program director here at Sakura TV,

25
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,486
received four tapes.

26
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:34,071
After a thorough examination,

27
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:36,698
there can be no doubt
that they are from Kira himself.

28
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:39,201
[Demegawa] Our audience ratings
should go up sixty…

29
00:02:39,326 --> 00:02:41,787
no, more like seventy percent
after this.

30
00:02:42,371 --> 00:02:44,665
[man on TV] The first tape we received
contained a prediction

31
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:47,668
regarding the time of death
of two suspected criminals

32
00:02:47,751 --> 00:02:49,378
who'd recently been arrested.

33
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:52,631
And as predicted,
at the exact time that Kira had specified,

34
00:02:52,756 --> 00:02:55,384
both men died suddenly of heart attacks
yesterday.

35
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:57,094
[Ryuzaki] If what they're saying is true,

36
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:59,513
it's clearly something
that only Kira could do.

37
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:03,058
[man on TV] Kira has instructed us
to air the second tape today

38
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:05,310
at exactly 5:59 PM.

39
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:07,771
And we do intend
to comply with his demands.

40
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:11,900
This tape should offer proof of his powers
by predicting yet another death.

41
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:14,194
Beyond that, we understand
that it contains a message

42
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:16,279
to all the people of the world from Kira.

43
00:03:16,488 --> 00:03:19,366
[gasps] This has to be another fake,
don't you think?

44
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:20,450
I doubt it.

45
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:23,245
I'm pretty sure even Sakura TV
wouldn't stoop that low.

46
00:03:23,662 --> 00:03:25,288
And now, the video.

47
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:32,713
[Kira clears throat]

48
00:03:32,963 --> 00:03:34,297
[Kira] I am Kira.

49
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:37,008
If this video was being aired
on April 18th,

50
00:03:37,092 --> 00:03:40,303
at exactly 5:59 PM, as I requested,

51
00:03:40,387 --> 00:03:45,514
then the time now is 5:59:47, 48, 49…

52
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:48,437
Please change the channel to Taiyo TV.

53
00:03:48,729 --> 00:03:51,064
The news anchor, Mr. Kazuhiko Hibima,

54
00:03:51,189 --> 00:03:53,567
will die of a heart attack
at exactly six o'clock.

55
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:54,943
-What?
-Change it!

56
00:03:55,277 --> 00:03:57,237
TAIYO TV

57
00:03:57,571 --> 00:03:58,613
[Matsuda] It can't be!

58
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:01,199
[TV staff shouting indistinctly]

59
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:02,659
How could he?

60
00:04:03,268 --> 00:04:04,770
Change the channel back.

61
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:07,456
-And I need you to bring us another TV.
-[Kira] Mr. Hibima continued to refer…

62
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:09,580
-Watari. No, make it two.
-[Kira] …to Kira as evil on air.

63
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,848
-[Watari] Yes.
-[Kira] This is punishment.

64
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:13,003
[Kira] I'll present you
with another victim.

65
00:04:13,128 --> 00:04:18,133
My next target is NHN TV commentator,
Mr. Seiji Kumaizumi,

66
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,677
who is scheduled to appear
in a live broadcast.

67
00:04:20,886 --> 00:04:22,929
He too has dared to defy Kira.

68
00:04:23,013 --> 00:04:25,223
-[Matsuda] R-- Ryuzaki!
-Change it to Channel 24!

69
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:27,476
[TV staff shouting indistinctly]

70
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:29,102
[Ryuzaki] Please, change it back.

71
00:04:30,312 --> 00:04:32,481
[Kira] Now that you have seen
proof of my powers,

72
00:04:32,564 --> 00:04:35,358
you should have no trouble believing
that I'm Kira.

73
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:39,321
[Ryuzaki] Kira said that he was going to
send a message to the people of the world.

74
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,323
[gasps] Stop this broadcast!

75
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:43,575
-We can't let him finish!
-[gasps]

76
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:45,702
[Ukita] Get Sakura TV on the line!

77
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:47,746
It's no good.

78
00:04:47,838 --> 00:04:51,313
I'm trying but none of my contacts
at the station have their phones on.

79
00:04:51,413 --> 00:04:53,151
Nobody is picking up
at the reception either.

80
00:04:54,177 --> 00:04:55,109
Damn it!

81
00:04:55,227 --> 00:04:56,797
[grunts] Ukita!

82
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:59,138
I'll stop that broadcast myself,
if that's what it takes!

83
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,386
[Kira] People of the world,
please listen to me.

84
00:05:03,762 --> 00:05:06,139
The last thing I want to do
is kill the innocent.

85
00:05:06,415 --> 00:05:08,959
I hate evil and love justice.

86
00:05:09,068 --> 00:05:12,568
I've always thought of the police
as allies, and not as enemies.

87
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:16,024
Damn you, Kira…

88
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:18,652
-[siren wailing]
-[Kira] I intend to create a new world,

89
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:21,238
a perfect world that is free from evil.

90
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,073
If you agree to join me in my mission,

91
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:24,866
I know we can make it happen.

92
00:05:25,116 --> 00:05:27,202
And as long as no one tries to catch me,

93
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:29,454
I promise that the innocent will not die.

94
00:05:29,538 --> 00:05:30,664
Come on!

95
00:05:31,081 --> 00:05:33,041
[Kira] Even if you don't agree with me,

96
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:36,628
all I ask is that you do not publicize
your views in the media.

97
00:05:36,795 --> 00:05:39,214
-If you can do that, you will be spared.
-[people whispering indistinctly]

98
00:05:39,631 --> 00:05:42,551
All you have to do now is be patient.

99
00:05:42,926 --> 00:05:45,762
I will create a better world
that we can all enjoy.

100
00:05:46,263 --> 00:05:48,515
Say goodbye to the world as you know it.

101
00:05:48,707 --> 00:05:51,776
Soon, we will have a new world
ruled by benevolence,

102
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:54,688
inhabited by kindhearted, honest people.

103
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:56,064
Try to imagine it.

104
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:57,983
A world where the police and I--

105
00:06:00,986 --> 00:06:02,153
Sachiko.

106
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:07,909
Darling, this can't be good
for your health.

107
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:09,828
Please, you have to rest.

108
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:14,165
Sachiko.

109
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:17,836
Like it or not, I'm still in charge
of the Kira Task Force.

110
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:20,964
[sighs]

111
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:26,052
-[tires screeching]
-[siren wailing]

112
00:06:27,262 --> 00:06:28,430
[Ukita panting]

113
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:31,349
[Ukita] Damn it! It's locked!

114
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:33,435
This is the police!

115
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:34,769
Open up!

116
00:06:37,022 --> 00:06:38,231
You idiots!

117
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:40,358
-[heart beating loudly]
-[groans]

118
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:45,071
[groans]

119
00:06:48,325 --> 00:06:49,993
[groans]

120
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:00,462
-[Aizawa] Hello?
-[reporter] We interrupt

121
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:01,838
-this program to bring you live…
-Damn, I'm still not getting through!

122
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:03,673
-[reporter] …outside Sakura TV studio.
-Huh?

123
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:05,133
Aizawa! Look!

124
00:07:07,719 --> 00:07:08,845
SAKURA TV

125
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:11,890
[gasps]

126
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:14,809
[reporter] As you can see, someone
has collapsed just outside the door!

127
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:17,687
Again, we're coming to you live
from the Sakura TV building!

128
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,731
[Aizawa] Ukita!

129
00:07:19,898 --> 00:07:21,066
Damn it.

130
00:07:21,191 --> 00:07:22,275
Kira did this.

131
00:07:23,652 --> 00:07:25,528
[grunts] Mr. Aizawa.

132
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,198
Where are you going?

133
00:07:28,657 --> 00:07:30,700
Where do you think?
I've got to go there!

134
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:33,620
[Ryuzaki] You can't.
Please, think about it rationally.

135
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:36,706
What? You want me
to just sit here and watch TV?

136
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:38,667
[Ryuzaki]
If this truly is the work of Kira,

137
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:40,961
you'll just meet the same fate
if you go there.

138
00:07:41,578 --> 00:07:44,622
You told us
that Kira couldn't kill without a name!

139
00:07:45,006 --> 00:07:46,591
So, how could this happen?

140
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:49,678
The aliases and fake police IDs
were worthless!

141
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:51,221
What are we gonna do, L?

142
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,564
You don't think Kira has
all our names already, do you?

143
00:07:53,714 --> 00:07:55,850
That's a definite possibility.

144
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:59,437
However, if that's the case,
you'd think it would be easier for him

145
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:02,399
to kill off the entire task force
before making a move.

146
00:08:02,616 --> 00:08:06,361
Initially, I deduced that Kira needed
both the name and the face to kill,

147
00:08:06,528 --> 00:08:08,279
but from what we've just seen,

148
00:08:08,363 --> 00:08:12,450
I'd say it's not entirely impossible
that Kira can kill with only a face.

149
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:15,245
All I know for sure is that Kira

150
00:08:15,412 --> 00:08:18,873
is either in that TV station,
or he's somewhere close by.

151
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,668
In a place where he can watch
everyone who enters the building.

152
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:24,212
-Perhaps--
-If Kira is in the area,

153
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,756
then isn't that why
we should get down there?

154
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:28,299
[Ryuzaki] For all we know,

155
00:08:28,383 --> 00:08:30,802
he could've just placed
surveillance cameras in the area.

156
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:32,637
If we rush down there unprepared,

157
00:08:32,804 --> 00:08:34,139
-all of us will be killed.
-Wasn't it you

158
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:36,933
who said we would have to
risk our life to catch Kira?

159
00:08:37,392 --> 00:08:39,060
I meant what I said, but…

160
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:40,770
risking my life to catch Kira

161
00:08:40,895 --> 00:08:43,064
and doing something
that I know will cost me my life,

162
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:44,524
are two entirely different things.

163
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:45,817
Oh, yeah?

164
00:08:50,405 --> 00:08:51,740
Please, control yourself.

165
00:08:52,282 --> 00:08:53,867
We've lost Ukita.

166
00:08:55,076 --> 00:08:56,453
I understand you wanna go there,

167
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,997
but if something was to happen
to you as well…

168
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,166
[sighs]

169
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:05,128
[Kira] I now await
a response from the police.

170
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:06,629
You must decide whether or not

171
00:09:06,713 --> 00:09:08,965
you will help me create
a better world for all of us.

172
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:12,802
Please announce your decision
on the six o'clock news in four days.

173
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:14,220
I prepared two videos.

174
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:16,473
One to be aired if the answer is "yes,"

175
00:09:16,598 --> 00:09:18,600
and another if the answer is "no."

176
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:20,477
Hm?

177
00:09:20,935 --> 00:09:21,811
[gasps]

178
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:24,898
[police siren wailing]

179
00:09:25,065 --> 00:09:27,108
[growling]

180
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,110
Huh?

181
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:35,033
[man screaming]

182
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,495
[groans]

183
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:42,582
What the hell is going on?

184
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:45,085
Hey! Step out of the vehicle!

185
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:46,920
[gasps]

186
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:48,755
The Kira video.

187
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,840
Show me which studio
they are broadcasting it from.

188
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:54,260
[reporter] A vehicle has just driven
through the front doors of the station!

189
00:09:55,804 --> 00:09:57,931
Well, that's one way
of getting into the building

190
00:09:58,014 --> 00:09:59,390
without being seen by Kira.

191
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:01,059
[Matsuda] But who would…

192
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:03,394
This is the police!

193
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:05,230
Stop this broadcast immediately!

194
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:06,231
Who are you?

195
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:08,817
Hand those tapes over to me!
Do you understand?

196
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,194
[Demegawa] Hold on, officer!
It's not that simple.

197
00:10:11,319 --> 00:10:12,612
My hands are tied here.

198
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:15,156
If we stop this broadcast,
he will kill all of us.

199
00:10:15,865 --> 00:10:16,825
Shut up!

200
00:10:16,908 --> 00:10:19,911
You're gonna be killed right here and now
if you don't give those tapes to me!

201
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:22,413
Wha-- Come on!
What the hell do you think you're doing?

202
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:24,457
This is crazy!

203
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:46,020
This is happening because you chose
to make Kira a celebrity!

204
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:48,857
You're getting exactly what you deserve!

205
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:50,692
-[gasping]
-I want every single copy you have.

206
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:52,610
And don't make me ask you again!

207
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:55,405
[Demegawa] I-- I got it!
I'll give them to you.

208
00:10:55,530 --> 00:10:58,324
No problem. Just please,
stop waving that gun around!

209
00:10:58,575 --> 00:11:00,410
You're acting like a madman!

210
00:11:00,577 --> 00:11:01,578
[siren wailing]

211
00:11:01,703 --> 00:11:03,788
[reporter gasps]
We're still outside Sakura TV.

212
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:06,166
As you can see,
a police car has just arrived.

213
00:11:06,249 --> 00:11:07,667
So, we are not alone.

214
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,294
There're still other officers out there

215
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:11,171
who are willing to stand up to Kira.

216
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:12,797
-[Ryuzaki] Mr. Aizawa.
-Huh?

217
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:16,509
You know Deputy Director Kitamura's
cell phone number, right?

218
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,720
[ringing]

219
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:23,892
Aizawa, I told you not to call me
on this phone.

220
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:25,435
-[L] This is L.
-[gasps]

221
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,562
There's something I need you to do for me.

222
00:11:27,729 --> 00:11:30,315
There may be police officers
who'll see this broadcast

223
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:32,775
and feel moved to take action
in the name of justice.

224
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:35,570
If you don't take control
of the situation quickly,

225
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:36,988
there will be a disaster.

226
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:40,498
But technically, we are not supposed
to be involved in this case.

227
00:11:40,836 --> 00:11:41,889
Huh?

228
00:11:44,037 --> 00:11:46,456
[reporter] Two police officers
have just collapsed on the sidewalk.

229
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:49,542
I think we may be in danger!
We are moving away from the scene.

230
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:53,087
I understand, L.

231
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:54,964
I see your point now.

232
00:11:55,048 --> 00:11:56,424
Tell me what I should do.

233
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:58,343
[phone ringing]

234
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,888
Detective Superintendent Yagami.

235
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,390
Call him back immediately,
and give me the phone.

236
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:07,101
I need to speak with Ryuzaki!

237
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:08,478
Yes, it's me.

238
00:12:08,603 --> 00:12:11,606
Mr. Yagami, so you're the one
driving the police van.

239
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:14,567
That's right.
I couldn't just sit and watch.

240
00:12:15,026 --> 00:12:18,404
I've confiscated all of the tapes.
I'm bringing them to you.

241
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:20,865
But what about your condition?
Are you all right?

242
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:22,575
I'm feeling just fine.

243
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:25,828
To be honest with you,
I don't think I've ever felt more alive.

244
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:28,164
So, what do you think I should do now?

245
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:30,708
I take going out the front
would be too dangerous.

246
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:33,127
But I could always
use the police van again.

247
00:12:33,378 --> 00:12:34,921
Please, hold the line for a second.

248
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:36,714
Deputy Director Kitamura,

249
00:12:36,923 --> 00:12:39,133
it was Chief Yagami
who just drove into the building.

250
00:12:39,384 --> 00:12:40,843
Are your preparations complete?

251
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:42,553
It's done, as you requested.

252
00:12:43,513 --> 00:12:45,723
Mr. Yagami, listen carefully.

253
00:12:45,807 --> 00:12:48,268
In exactly five minutes, I want you
to come out the front entrance.

254
00:12:48,393 --> 00:12:50,270
You want me
to exit through the front entrance?

255
00:13:00,238 --> 00:13:02,782
[footsteps echoing]

256
00:13:10,665 --> 00:13:11,749
[gasps]

257
00:13:17,672 --> 00:13:19,424
[police officer]
Make sure there are no gaps!

258
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:21,551
Do not reveal your faces!

259
00:13:21,843 --> 00:13:23,970
We know that Kira is not in the building.

260
00:13:24,178 --> 00:13:25,388
He's outside!

261
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:38,943
Thank you.

262
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,237
I'll drive myself.

263
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:42,905
[Ide] I understand.

264
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:50,955
[police officer] Listen up!

265
00:13:51,122 --> 00:13:54,834
There is a very good chance that Kira
is still in the vicinity of the station!

266
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:57,337
As you move out, proceed with caution.

267
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:59,547
You are not to remove your helmets!

268
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:04,886
[Koki] There you have it.
The police refuse to cooperate with Kira.

269
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:06,804
Instead, they're preparing to fight.

270
00:14:06,888 --> 00:14:10,308
And as much
as I fear for my own life in saying so,

271
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,684
this is right!

272
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,520
And it must be done.

273
00:14:14,729 --> 00:14:17,899
Kira has become a threat
to our very constitution.

274
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:20,985
And as citizens, we must fight back!

275
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:24,238
I am NHN's Golden News anchor,

276
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:26,199
Koki Tanakabara!

277
00:14:26,824 --> 00:14:27,867
-[door opens]
-Huh?

278
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,994
-Chief Yagami!
-[Ryuzaki] Welcome back, Chief.

279
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:33,081
[grunts] Ryuzaki,

280
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:36,376
I apologize for taking matters
into my own hands.

281
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:39,212
I have to admit,
I got a little bit carried away.

282
00:14:39,754 --> 00:14:41,089
-No.
-Here.

283
00:14:41,339 --> 00:14:43,174
These are all of the tapes
in an envelope.

284
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:45,593
Everything Kira sent to the station
is in here.

285
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,220
[Ryuzaki] I can't thank you enough.

286
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:50,848
I think I'd better rest for a minute.
[groans]

287
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:54,268
[Ryuzaki] Mr. Yagami…

288
00:14:54,477 --> 00:14:56,104
This won't go to waste.

289
00:14:57,238 --> 00:14:59,371
The postmark is from Osaka.

290
00:14:59,941 --> 00:15:02,777
But Kira can control his victims
before they die.

291
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:07,031
So, he could have delivered it from Osaka
without going there himself.

292
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:09,033
Mr. Aizawa.

293
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,369
Can you please take this
to the crime lab right away?

294
00:15:11,661 --> 00:15:13,579
I still have a couple of friends
down there.

295
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:15,581
I'll make sure they
go over every inch of this.

296
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:17,041
That's good. Please, do so.

297
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:18,042
While you're doing that,

298
00:15:18,126 --> 00:15:20,920
I'm going to watch these tapes
to see if they can tell us anything.

299
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:26,968
[Yagami] Well, what do you make of these?

300
00:15:27,135 --> 00:15:29,011
They were definitely interesting.

301
00:15:29,554 --> 00:15:33,057
If the police had said "yes,"
and agreed to cooperate with Kira,

302
00:15:33,141 --> 00:15:35,143
tape number three
was supposed to be aired.

303
00:15:35,226 --> 00:15:37,478
Tape four if the answer was "no".

304
00:15:38,229 --> 00:15:40,523
Tape three covers
the terms of cooperation.

305
00:15:40,648 --> 00:15:44,235
Put simply, he is requesting that
we broadcast the names of more criminals.

306
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:47,780
He seems particularly interested
in those who have assaulted others,

307
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,490
or those who have somehow hurt

308
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:52,160
or taken advantage
of the weak and defenseless.

309
00:15:52,368 --> 00:15:56,289
Of course, Kira would
play the role of judge in all of this.

310
00:15:56,456 --> 00:15:59,736
Furthermore, as proof that
the police are willing to cooperate,

311
00:15:59,884 --> 00:16:02,804
he wants police officials and L
to appear on TV

312
00:16:03,004 --> 00:16:06,215
to make a public announcement
that we plan to cooperate with him.

313
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:07,467
Huh?

314
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:10,444
[Ryuzaki] He needs us to reveal our faces.

315
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:13,264
That way, he can kill us
if the police do anything suspicious.

316
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,725
In other words,
he will hold our lives as insurance.

317
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:17,351
I see.

318
00:16:17,435 --> 00:16:19,187
So, what about
the content of the fourth video

319
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:20,952
if we were to answer "no"?

320
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:24,233
The wording was different
but he more or less says the same thing.

321
00:16:24,866 --> 00:16:28,279
Mr. Yagami, it should go without saying
that the answer is "no".

322
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:31,449
Please, have someone take tape number four
over to Sakura TV

323
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:33,723
and authorize them to broadcast it.

324
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,872
[Kira] I can only say it's a shame
that your answer is "no."

325
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:40,541
It's clear that the police
wish to oppose me.

326
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:42,460
This will not go unpunished.

327
00:16:42,627 --> 00:16:44,587
So, I will start by taking the life

328
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:47,256
of either of the Director-General
of the NPA,

329
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:48,799
or the detective known as L,

330
00:16:48,925 --> 00:16:51,344
who is currently
leading the investigation against me.

331
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:54,096
The Director-General or L.

332
00:16:54,597 --> 00:16:56,307
Who will pay the price for your refusal

333
00:16:56,474 --> 00:16:58,934
to cooperate in the creation
of the peaceful world?

334
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:01,109
You have four days to decide.

335
00:17:05,316 --> 00:17:07,526
[chuckles quietly]

336
00:17:08,246 --> 00:17:09,259
[sighs]

337
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:13,991
It looks like I've even got God
on my side now.

338
00:17:14,299 --> 00:17:16,452
Well, I suppose it's actually

339
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:17,912
a God of Death.

340
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:20,039
[chuckles] Seems like it.

341
00:17:20,482 --> 00:17:24,168
It would appear that another Shinigami
has come to the human world.

342
00:17:24,279 --> 00:17:26,721
And somehow that Shinigami's Death Note

343
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:29,674
has fallen into the hands of
someone who agrees with Kira.

344
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:33,741
And this person most likely
has the Shinigami-eyes,

345
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:35,846
which makes him very deadly.

346
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:38,474
His power to kill surpasses even mine.

347
00:17:38,766 --> 00:17:40,935
One thing is for certain.
If I leave things,

348
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:44,063
I'm pretty sure that L would be
finished off within the next four days.

349
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:45,523
However…

350
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:47,942
I can't forgive this impostor

351
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:51,529
for the way he's tarnishing Kira's image
with these senseless killings.

352
00:17:51,821 --> 00:17:54,073
Not to mention,
if he slips up and gets caught,

353
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:56,909
the Death Note could be discovered,
and that I cannot allow.

354
00:17:56,993 --> 00:17:59,620
I can't afford to leave him alone
for much longer.

355
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:02,248
[cackles]

356
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:05,418
Therefore, what needs to happen very soon

357
00:18:05,904 --> 00:18:08,045
is for me to join the task force.

358
00:18:08,296 --> 00:18:10,256
It will allow me to keep track of L

359
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,049
and this fake Kira.

360
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:18,556
Ryuzaki, I'm afraid it's as you thought.

361
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:21,376
Several of our member countries
have weighed in

362
00:18:21,476 --> 00:18:25,137
and it seems they're in favor
of having the real L appear on TV.

363
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:30,276
I think that's the most appropriate choice
given the options.

364
00:18:30,776 --> 00:18:33,112
Well, we still have three days
before it happens.

365
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:35,448
Maybe we can find
some countermeasure.

366
00:18:35,573 --> 00:18:38,034
After all of this,
it would really annoy me…

367
00:18:39,427 --> 00:18:43,002
if I'm killed by the first person
who jumped on the Kira's bandwagon.

368
00:18:43,414 --> 00:18:45,833
-Ryuzaki, what do you mean by that?
-[swallows]

369
00:18:46,584 --> 00:18:49,993
That there is a strong possibility
that this Kira is a fake.

370
00:18:50,421 --> 00:18:53,507
No, we should think of him
more as a second Kira.

371
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:55,134
A second Kira?

372
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:59,013
I-- I don't understand.
Why do you think there's a copycat?

373
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:01,140
How did you come to that conclusion?

374
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:03,017
[Ryuzaki] I looked at the victims

375
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:05,186
he used as predictions on tape number one.

376
00:19:05,269 --> 00:19:09,190
Their purpose was to prove
to Sakura TV staff that he is Kira.

377
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:13,361
Both their names were only reported
in tabloids and daytime talk-shows,

378
00:19:13,444 --> 00:19:15,446
so they weren't exactly
hardened criminals.

379
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:18,157
The real Kira
has no need to prove himself

380
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,368
using such insignificant criminals.

381
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:22,578
But from the perspective
of the Second Kira…

382
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:24,038
[gulps]

383
00:19:24,639 --> 00:19:26,207
He'd wanna make absolutely certain

384
00:19:26,332 --> 00:19:28,000
that he didn't predict
the death of a criminal

385
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:30,211
who could be killed
by the real Kira first.

386
00:19:30,378 --> 00:19:32,213
Hmm… Ryuzaki,

387
00:19:32,380 --> 00:19:33,798
If you had to put a number on it,

388
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:36,175
what's the probability of a second Kira?

389
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,637
[Ryuzaki] This time, I'd say
it's more than 70 percent.

390
00:19:40,554 --> 00:19:43,057
I really don't like the way he operates.

391
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:44,475
It's not like Kira.

392
00:19:44,742 --> 00:19:45,826
Not like him?

393
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:47,144
[Ryuzaki] In the past,

394
00:19:47,228 --> 00:19:49,522
he has traditionally
avoided killing innocent people,

395
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:52,191
with the exception of those
who were trying to catch him.

396
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:54,652
Anyway, if we can capture one Kira,

397
00:19:54,777 --> 00:19:56,862
I think that will provide us
with a lot of insight

398
00:19:56,946 --> 00:19:58,531
into how we can find the other one.

399
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:00,916
Mr. Yagami.

400
00:20:01,409 --> 00:20:03,327
I'd like your permission to ask your son

401
00:20:03,411 --> 00:20:05,663
to cooperate with us
in this investigation?

402
00:20:05,788 --> 00:20:06,664
[gasping]

403
00:20:06,731 --> 00:20:10,818
If you want my son to join the task force,
does this mean you no longer suspect him?

404
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:13,963
Well, I can't say
that he's been completely cleared,

405
00:20:14,088 --> 00:20:16,924
but his deductive abilities would be
invaluable to us right now.

406
00:20:17,842 --> 00:20:19,427
[Yagami] So that's what it means.

407
00:20:20,386 --> 00:20:23,723
If my son wants to cooperate with you,
then I have no reason to prevent it.

408
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:26,684
[Ryuzaki] I appreciate that.
However…

409
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:30,604
please don't tell him that we think
this latest Kira might be a fake.

410
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:32,690
I don't want him to know that yet.

411
00:20:33,149 --> 00:20:36,736
We want to make it appear to him
that we're still chasing the same Kira.

412
00:20:36,861 --> 00:20:38,237
[sighing]

413
00:20:43,315 --> 00:20:44,493
[Shinigami] Misa.

414
00:20:44,744 --> 00:20:46,704
I gave that Death Note to you,

415
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:49,320
so why not use it for yourself?

416
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:53,491
[Misa] I am using it for myself.

417
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:56,005
Because I believe in what Kira is doing.

418
00:20:56,213 --> 00:20:58,674
I want to know what kind
of person Kira is.

419
00:20:58,883 --> 00:21:00,843
I want to meet him and talk to him.

420
00:21:01,193 --> 00:21:04,657
That's the only reason I sent all those
videos to that TV station.

421
00:21:04,847 --> 00:21:07,475
I had to find some way
to make Kira notice me.

422
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:11,030
And I'd say that probably
got his attention.

423
00:21:11,225 --> 00:21:12,602
Don't you think? [chuckles]

424
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:14,982
It's a dangerous game you're playing.

425
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:17,042
There's a chance you could be killed.

426
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:18,611
Do you understand?

427
00:21:18,711 --> 00:21:22,000
[Misa] It's all right. I'm sure that Kira
is kind to those with pure hearts.

428
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:26,045
And if it came down to that,
I'm still stronger than he is

429
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:28,662
because I have the eyes!

430
00:21:30,498 --> 00:21:36,504
TO BE CONTINUED

431
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:47,014
[theme music playing]

432
00:22:48,044 --> 00:22:49,422
[theme music concludes]
